----- FILE: ./README.md -----
# Milkdropper 🎨🎵

**Pure Rust audio visualization library inspired by Milkdrop2**

[![Rust](https://img.shields.io/badge/rust-1.75%2B-orange.svg)](https://www.rust-lang.org/)
[![License](https://img.shields.io/badge/license-MIT%2FApache--2.0-blue.svg)](LICENSE)
[![Status](https://img.shields.io/badge/status-in%20development-yellow.svg)](https://github.com/yourusername/milkdropper)

---

## What is Milkdropper?

Milkdropper is a **library-first**, **cross-platform** audio visualization engine written in pure Rust. It reimagines the classic Milkdrop2 visualizer with modern architecture:

- 🎵 **Real-time audio analysis** using the Phoenix Marine algorithm (no FFT libraries!)
- 🎨 **GPU-accelerated rendering** with wgpu (Vulkan/Metal/DX12/WebGPU)
- 📝 **Preset compatibility** - Load and render .milk preset files
- 🔒 **Safe expression evaluation** - Sandboxed preset scripting
- 🌍 **Cross-platform** - Linux, macOS, Windows (ESP32 target planned)
- 📦 **Library-first design** - Embed visualization in your application

---

## Project Status

**Phase**: 🏗️ **Rust Architecture Complete** (Phase 1)

**Completed**:
- ✅ C++ Archaeological Analysis (original Milkdrop2 codebase mapped)
- ✅ System Architecture Design (components, data flow, threading)
- ✅ Module Structure Design (5-crate workspace)
- ✅ Public API Design (3 levels of abstraction)
- ✅ Dependency Analysis (pure Rust, no FFT libraries)
- ✅ Initial Cargo.toml Setup

**Next Phase**: Implementation (Phoenix Marine Integration)

---

## Architecture

Milkdropper is organized as a Cargo workspace with 5 crates:

```
milkdropper/
├── crates/
│   ├── milkdropper/        # Main library (public API)
│   ├── milkdropper-audio/  # Audio analysis (Phoenix Marine)
│   ├── milkdropper-preset/ # Preset engine (parser + evaluator)
│   ├── milkdropper-render/ # Rendering engine (wgpu + software)
│   └── milkdropper-cli/    # CLI tool (example app)
├── analysis/               # C++ codebase analysis
├── design/                 # Architecture documentation
│   ├── architecture.md     # System design (14,700 words)
│   ├── module_structure.md # Module organization (11,200 words)
│   ├── api_design.md       # API specification (15,800 words)
│   ├── dependencies.md     # Dependency analysis (8,400 words)
│   └── SUMMARY.md          # Design summary
├── tests/                  # Integration tests
├── benches/                # Performance benchmarks
└── examples/               # Example applications
```

**Total Design Documentation**: 50,100 words of architectural specs!

---

## Quick Start (Future)

Once implemented, usage will be as simple as:

```rust
use milkdropper::{Visualizer, Config};

fn main() -> Result<(), Box<dyn std::error::Error>> {
    // 1. Create visualizer
    let mut viz = Visualizer::new(Config::default())?;

    // 2. Load preset
    viz.load_preset("presets/default.milk")?;

    // 3. Render loop
    loop {
        let audio_samples = get_audio();  // Your audio source
        let frame = viz.render(audio_samples)?;
        display(frame);  // Your display logic
    }
}
```

---

## Key Features

### 🎵 Audio Analysis
- **Phoenix Marine algorithm** (no FFT libraries per project requirements)
- Bass/mid/treble band extraction
- Temporal smoothing (exponential moving averages)
- Supports up to **192kHz audio** (higher than original 44.1kHz)
- **<1ms processing time** per frame

### 🎨 Rendering
- **wgpu backend** - Modern GPU API (Vulkan/Metal/DX12/WebGPU)
- **Software fallback** - CPU-only rendering for headless/testing
- Custom waveforms, shapes, and sprites
- Warp/blur/composite effects
- Shader support (WGSL)

### 📝 Preset System
- Parse .milk preset files (INI-style format)
- **Safe expression evaluation** (sandboxed bytecode VM)
- Compatible with original Milkdrop2 presets
- Preset transitions and blending
- Programmatic preset creation via builder API

### 🔒 Security
- Sandboxed expression evaluation (instruction limits, timeouts)
- No arbitrary code execution
- Memory limits per preset
- Regular dependency audits

### 🌍 Cross-Platform
- Linux, macOS, Windows (tier 1 support)
- WebAssembly (future)
- ESP32 (future embedded target)

---

## Design Principles

1. **Library-first** - Not tied to specific UI or audio framework
2. **Type-safe** - Leverage Rust's type system to prevent errors
3. **Zero-copy** - Minimize allocations in hot paths
4. **Real-time** - Audio processing never drops frames
5. **Composable** - Use components independently
6. **Extensible** - Plugin system for custom effects

---

## Performance Targets

| Component | Target | Max | Notes |
|-----------|--------|-----|-------|
| Phoenix Marine | 0.5ms | 1.0ms | Core audio analysis |
| Preset Eval | 0.5ms | 1.0ms | Expression VM |
| Rendering | 10ms | 16ms | 60 FPS target |
| **Total** | **11ms** | **18ms** | Real-time capable |

**Memory Budget**:
- Desktop: <50 MB
- ESP32 (future): <5 MB

