### 4.2 Audio Crate (`milkdropper-audio`)

```toml
[features]
default = []

# SIMD acceleration
simd = ["simdeez"]

# no_std support (for ESP32)
no-std = []
```

---

### 4.3 Rendering Crate (`milkdropper-render`)

```toml
[features]
default = ["wgpu-backend"]

# Rendering backends
wgpu-backend = ["wgpu", "bytemuck"]
software-backend = ["tiny-skia"]

# Shader features
shader-cache = []        # Cache compiled shaders
shader-hot-reload = []   # Hot-reload shaders (development)
```

---

## 5. Public API Surface

### 5.1 High-Level API (Simple)

**For users who just want it to work**:

```rust
use milkdropper::{Visualizer, Config};

fn main() -> Result<(), Box<dyn std::error::Error>> {
    // 1. Create visualizer with default config
    let mut viz = Visualizer::new(Config::default())?;

    // 2. Load preset
    viz.load_preset("presets/default.milk")?;

    // 3. Process audio and render
    loop {
        let audio_samples = get_audio();  // User provides
        let frame = viz.render(audio_samples)?;
        display(frame);  // User handles
    }
}
```

---

### 5.2 Mid-Level API (Configurable)

**For users who want control**:

```rust
use milkdropper::{Visualizer, Config, AudioConfig, RenderConfig};

fn main() -> Result<(), Box<dyn std::error::Error>> {
    let config = Config {
        audio: AudioConfig {
            sample_rate: 192000,
            buffer_size: 1024,
            ..Default::default()
        },
        render: RenderConfig {
            fps: 60,
            resolution: (1920, 1080),
            backend: RenderBackendType::Wgpu,
        },
        ..Default::default()
    };

    let mut viz = Visualizer::with_config(config)?;
    viz.load_preset("preset.milk")?;

    // Configure preset blending
    viz.set_transition_duration(5.0);  // 5 seconds

    loop {
        let audio_samples = get_audio();
        let frame = viz.render(audio_samples)?;

        // Optional: access audio analysis data
        let audio_frame = viz.last_audio_frame();
        println!("Bass: {}", audio_frame.bass);

        display(frame);
    }
}
```

---

### 5.3 Low-Level API (Full Control)

**For users who want everything**:

```rust
use milkdropper_audio::{AudioAnalyzer, AudioFrame};
use milkdropper_preset::{PresetEngine, Preset};
use milkdropper_render::{Renderer, RenderBackend};

fn main() -> Result<(), Box<dyn std::error::Error>> {
    // 1. Create components separately
    let mut analyzer = AudioAnalyzer::new(192000);
    let mut preset_engine = PresetEngine::new();
    let mut renderer = Renderer::new(RenderBackend::Wgpu)?;

    // 2. Load preset manually
    let preset_text = std::fs::read_to_string("preset.milk")?;
    let preset = Preset::parse(&preset_text)?;
    preset_engine.load(preset)?;

    // 3. Process audio and render manually
    loop {
        // Audio analysis
        let audio_samples = get_audio();
        let audio_frame = analyzer.process(audio_samples)?;

        // Preset evaluation
        preset_engine.update(&audio_frame)?;
        let preset_state = preset_engine.state();

        // Rendering
        let render_frame = renderer.render(preset_state)?;

        display(render_frame);
    }
}
```

---

## 6. Module Visibility

### 6.1 Public Exports (`milkdropper`)

**What users can access**:

```rust
// Main types
pub use visualizer::Visualizer;
pub use config::Config;
pub use error::VisualizerError;

// Re-exported from sub-crates
pub use milkdropper_audio::{AudioAnalyzer, AudioFrame};
pub use milkdropper_preset::{Preset, PresetEngine, PresetError};
pub use milkdropper_render::{Renderer, RenderFrame};

// Utilities
pub mod util {
    pub use crate::state::VisualizerState;
}
```

---

### 6.2 Internal Modules (Private)

**Not exposed to users**:

```rust
// milkdropper-audio internals
mod marine;              // Phoenix Marine algorithm
mod extractor;           // Band extraction
mod smoother;            // Smoothing logic

// milkdropper-preset internals
mod parser;              // .milk parsing
mod eval;                // Expression VM
mod types;               // Internal types

// milkdropper-render internals
mod backend;             // Backend implementations
mod primitives;          // Drawing primitives
mod effects;             // Visual effects
```

